President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday in Daura, Katsina State, said Nigeria’s socio-economic and political salvation would come from education. The President’s Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Malam Garba Shehu, in a statement in Abuja on Monday, said the president stated this at an event to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the founding of Community Secondary School, Daura. Buhari and five others founded the school as a community service. The president urged Nigerians to embrace learning as a way of life as his administration would do its best to provide access to it. ALSO READ: Insurgency: Buhari launches made-in-Nigeria mine-resistant armored vehicles Buhari, who was honoured at the event, said his nine years in boarding school and joining the army shaped his life. President Buhari, First Lady Aisha, 30 years after and… President Buhari departs Daura Buhari lauds Katsina Govt. for road construction, says… Buhari to flag off 2019 Anti-Corruption Marathon in Abuja “I spent nine years in the boarding school where the teachers showered us with love, care and total commitment. They treated you like their own children. “They commended you when you did well, and flogged you on bare buttocks if you misbehaved,” the President said. He praised the current management of the school, which has been renamed Pilot Secondary School, Daura, for maintaining high standards. Buhari implored the old boys association to carry on the good work they were doing which had raised the school to an enviable height. Alhaji M.T. Bature, the Sarkin Kudu of Katsina, said the vision of the founding fathers had ensured the success of so many sons of the state. He said graduate of the school had become professors, engineers, doctors and military generals. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
